{"word":"H6718 - צַיִד - tsayid - tsah'-yid - [idiom] catcheth","slug":"H6718","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">צַיִד</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>tsayid"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>tsah'-yid"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>[idiom] catcheth"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E6;&#x05D9;&#x05D3; - tsayid</b> - <i>tsah'-yid</i><p/>From a form of <a href=\"#/H6679\">H6679</a> and meaning the same; the <i>chase</i>; also <i>game</i> (thus taken); (generally) <i>lunch</i> (especially for a journey): -  X catcheth, food, X hunter, (that which he took in) hunting, venison, victuals."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6679\">H6679</a>, <a href=\"#/H6720\">H6720</a>, <a href=\"#/H6737\">H6737</a>"}]}